Two Chinese nationals have been arrested with 800 litres of methanol and over 3,000 litres of chang'aa and busaa in Machakos. The two, Wang Yalan and  Wang Haijian were arrested in there residence at  Green Park in Machakos. Detectives from  Machakos made the arrest after a tip-off from the public. During the arrest, several sacks of sorghum, rice, drums of sorghum mixtures kept to Ferment and several huge water tanks. A Liquor Processing Plant was also found in their homestead. The two are now in custody and the goods found during the arrest kept as exhibits.